28/03/2011
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The trial of former Chief of General Staff of the Yugoslav Army Momcilo Perisic is entering its final stage Monday (March 28th) at The Hague war crimes tribunal, with the prosecution and the defence expected to present their closing arguments. Perisic stands accused of crimes against humanity and war crimes committed between 1993 and 1995 during the conflicts in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia. He surrendered to authorities in 2005. His trial began in October 2008. (B92, Tanjug, Fena - 28/03/11)
